- Write a "listpath" function that lists all your path components, one per line:

  $ echo $PATH
  /home/jhaemer/bin:/usr/local/bin:/usr/bin:/bin:/usr/games:/home/jhaemer/bin:/usr/local/bin:/usr/bin:/bin:/usr/games
  $ listpath
  /home/jhaemer/bin
  /usr/local/bin
  /usr/bin
  /bin
  /usr/games
  /home/jhaemer/bin
  /usr/local/bin
  /usr/bin
  /bin
  /usr/games

Could this be a script?

- Write a uniqpath script that removes duplicates

  $ echo $PATH
  /home/jhaemer/bin:/usr/local/bin:/usr/bin:/bin:/usr/games:/home/jhaemer/bin:/usr/local/bin:/usr/bin:/bin:/usr/games:
  $ uniqpath
  /home/jhaemer/bin:/usr/local/bin:/usr/bin:/bin:/usr/games

Could this be a function?
    
- Write a cleanpath function that cleans your path

  $ echo $PATH
  /home/jhaemer/bin:/usr/local/bin:/usr/bin:/bin:/usr/games:/home/jhaemer/bin:/usr/local/bin:/usr/bin:/bin:/usr/games:
  $ cleanpath
  $ echo $PATH
  /home/jhaemer/bin:/usr/local/bin:/usr/bin:/bin:/usr/games

Could this be a script?
